# Sentry

Sentry observes execution boundaries; it is never imported by domain or application code.

## Instrumentation

- Initialize client and server SDKs in framework entrypoints/composition using validated environment/bindings.
- Instrument route handlers, server functions, queue/cron stages, EA provider calls, and email dispatch with operation-specific spans.
- Propagate `trace_id`, `request_id`, job ID, event type/version, and a safe opaque tenant correlation value.
- Expected domain failures are controlled outcomes or low-severity breadcrumbs, not noisy exceptions.
- Disable event delivery when no DSN is configured; local development must still work.

## Allowlist and redaction

Only send explicitly allowlisted attributes. Before every event, breadcrumb, replay, and trace, remove:

- raw EA provider payloads and unsanitized match bodies;
- cookies, authorization headers, session IDs, tokens, provider secrets, and idempotency credentials;
- email addresses, real names, phone numbers, and platform identifiers not approved for telemetry;
- database dumps, SQL parameters, and private object keys;
- selection/dispute free-text that can identify participants beyond approved correlation.

Apply server-side `beforeSend`/`beforeBreadcrumb` redaction. Keep request-body capture and session replay off for authentication, EA sync, and notification routes unless a reviewed scrubber proves safety.

## Tags and messages

- Prefer bounded tags such as operation, route template, job stage, result state, provider health, and error code.
- Do not tag raw actor, organization, competition, encounter, or team IDs.
- User-visible errors use localized safe codes and `requestId`.
